 ## Background
 
 Auth0 notified us of deprecation changes affecting the `ministryofjustice@eu` tenant via email along with notifications from AWS. This is summarised in ticket https://github.com/ministryofjustice/modernisation-platform/issues/13150.
 Two separate deprecations were identified and resolved.
 
 ---
 
 ## 1: Legacy Management of Connection's Enabled Clients
 
 ### What was deprecated
 The `enabled_clients` field was being removed from the following Management API endpoints:
 - `GET /api/v2/connections`
 - `GET /api/v2/connections/{id}`
 - `PATCH /api/v2/connections/{id}`
 
 **End of life:** July 13, 2026
 
 ### Investigation
 
 - Reviewed the Terraform module [`moj-terraform-aws-sso`](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/moj-terraform-aws-sso) — no explicit use of `enabled_clients` in any Terraform resources
 - Confirmed the Auth0 Terraform provider in use was `v1.43.0` (via `.terraform.lock.hcl` in [`aws-root-account`](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/aws-root-account)) — above the required `v1.29.0` threshold per the [Auth0 migration guide](https://auth0.com/docs/troubleshoot/product-lifecycle/deprecations-and-migrations/migrate-dedicated-connection-endpoints)
 - Reviewed provider source code — confirmed `auth0_connection` resource does not use `enabled_clients`; the provider already uses the dedicated `GET /api/v2/connections/{id}/clients` endpoint
 - Checked Auth0 tenant logs with query:
   ``` type:depnote AND description:Legacy\ Management\ of\ Connection's\ Enabled\ Clients* ```

 - Depnotes were linked to the "Terraform Machine to Machine" client — triggered because the tenant migration toggle was still ON, causing Auth0 to include enabled_clients in all connection responses and log a depnote each time
 - Reviewed a Terraform plan run (https://github.com/ministryofjustice/aws-root-account/actions/runs/28439111898/job/84272262153) — all Auth0 resources refreshed cleanly with no errors or planned changes

 ### Resolution

 - Navigated to Auth0 Dashboard → Tenant Settings → Advanced → Migrations
 - Toggled off "Legacy Management of Connection's Enabled Clients"
 - Verified no new depnote log entries appeared after the next Terraform plan run

No code changes required

