## 2: New Management API Scopes Required for Connection Options

### What was deprecated

Requests to Management API connection endpoints require new scopes to access the options field:

 - read:connections_options — required for GET /api/v2/connections and GET /api/v2/connections/{id}
 - update:connections_options — required for PATCH /api/v2/connections/{id}

End of life: July 8, 2025

### Investigation

 - Identified depnote log entries with query:
   ``` type:depnote AND description:New\ Management\ API\ Scopes\ Required\ for\ Connection\ Options* ```
 - Log entries were linked to the "Terraform" application's client ID — the bootstrap M2M client used by the Terraform Auth0 provider to authenticate and manage resources (credentials stored in AWS Secrets Manager as auth0_saml)
 - Confirmed this is a separate client from auth0_client.idp_token ("Management API: Auth0") which is managed by the Terraform module and used by Auth0 Actions at login time
 - Searched all non-archived ministryofjustice (https://github.com/ministryofjustice) repositories — confirmed neither read:connections_options nor update:connections_options are defined in code anywhere across the organisation
 - The "Terraform" application client grants are not managed by Terraform (bootstrap credentials cannot manage themselves)

### Resolution

 - Navigated to Auth0 Dashboard → Applications → Applications → Terraform → APIs tab
 - Expanded the Auth0 Management API dropdown
 - Added the following scopes to the client grant:
   - read:connections_options
   - update:connections_options
 - Verified no new depnote log entries appeared after the next Terraform plan run

No code changes required

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Outcome

Both deprecations were resolved through Auth0 dashboard configuration changes only. No Terraform code changes were required. Post-resolution monitoring confirmed no new deprecation notices are appearing in the Auth0 tenant logs.

